      "content": "The distinction between bias and fake news has largely collapsed in the public eye, as both are often conflated into a single label of \"misinformation.\" While some content is intentionally deceptive, many instances of \"fake news\" are simply the result of systematic bias, confirmation bias, or algorithmic amplification that prioritizes engagement over accuracy. This conflation makes it nearly impossible for the average person to distinguish between a genuine lie and a biased opinion, effectively eroding the concept of objective truth in the digital age.",
